## highlight_min

> `highlight_min(in_col, scope="column", color=None, fill="lightblue", exclude=None)`

Highlight the minimum value in each selected column.

| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |
|-----------|------|---------|-------------|
| `in_col` | str \| list \| Expr | ŌĆö | Column(s) to apply to |
| `scope` | `"column"` \| `"table"` | `"column"` | Compute min per column or across all selected columns |
| `color` | str \| None | `None` | Text colour (auto-contrast if None) |
| `fill` | str | `"lightblue"` | Background fill colour |
| `exclude` | str \| list \| None | `None` | Columns to exclude |

**Example:**

```python
df.style().highlight_min("Profit").show()
```

{{ read_html('snippets/api_highlight_min_ex1.html') }}

