## highlight_above

> `highlight_above(in_col, value, inclusive=False, scope="column", color=None, fill="yellow")`

Highlight values strictly above (or equal to, if `inclusive=True`) a threshold.

| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |
|-----------|------|---------|-------------|
| `in_col` | str \| list \| Expr | ŌĆö | Column(s) to apply to |
| `value` | float | ŌĆö | Threshold value |
| `inclusive` | bool | `False` | Include the threshold value itself |
| `scope` | `"column"` \| `"table"` | `"column"` | Unused for this method (kept for API consistency) |
| `color` | str \| None | `None` | Text colour |
| `fill` | str | `"yellow"` | Background fill colour |

**Example:**

```python
df.style().highlight_above("Growth", value=10.0).show()
```

{{ read_html('snippets/api_highlight_above_ex1.html') }}

---

