## highlight_equal

> `highlight_equal(in_col, value, color=None, fill="yellow")`

Highlight cells whose value exactly equals the target.

| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |
|-----------|------|---------|-------------|
| `in_col` | str \| list \| Expr | ŌĆö | Column(s) to apply to |
| `value` | float \| str | ŌĆö | Target value |
| `color` | str \| None | `None` | Text colour |
| `fill` | str | `"yellow"` | Background fill colour |

**Example:**

```python
df.style().highlight_equal("Employees_k", value=150).show()
```

{{ read_html('snippets/api_highlight_equal_ex1.html') }}

